JOHANNESBURG - Drought-stricken Capetonians face even more stringent water restrictions from Saturday.Officials have imposed level 4B restrictions, limiting residents' water usage to less than 87-litres per person per day.READ: Cape Town mayor prays for rainOfficials list a number of suggestions to save water, including flushing toilets only when necessary and keeping showering shorter than two minutes.Dam levels in the Western Cape remain critically low and water supply needs to be built up during the winter.The City of Cape Town says it is monitoring consumers with higher than average usage and will install water limiters if consumption isn't reduced. eNCA